node.title: Police search for Auckland man missing since Monday
node.description: Counties Manakau police are appealing for information on 52-year-old Auckland man, Nicholas Nadin, who was reported missing on Monday.
node.content:
["Counties Manakau police are appealing for information on 52-year-old Auckland man, Nicholas Nadin, who was reported missing on Monday.", "", "
Aucklander Nicholas Nadin has been missing since 17 January, 2022. Photo: Supplied / NZ Police
", "In a statement, police said Nadin was last seen at Lloyd Elsmore Park in Pakuranga at 11am on Monday.", "Nadin is known to frequent the areas of Musick Point, Bucklands Beach, Half Moon Bay and Maraetai and police ask anyone who sees him to phone 111.", "He is described as 169cm tall and of stocky build and was last known to be wearing black trackpants, a black singlet and a black hoodie with a fish skeleton printed on the front.", "Police made multiple inquiries in the area since he was reported missing on Monday, but his whereabouts remain unknown and they are now concerned for the man's welfare.", "Police urge anyone with information about his whereabouts or possible sightings of him since Monday morning is asked to call them on 105, quoting file number 220117/4635."]
